In index.html find the Features page
(#page-features). It has 5 feature rows
numbered 01 through 05. Each row has a
text side and a visual demo panel side.

Replace the visual demo panel in each
feature row with the corresponding image
from the folder at:
~/Desktop/thrive stuff/

The images are named:
thriveimage1.png — row 01 / Profile
thriveimage2.png — row 02 / Connect
thriveimage3.png — row 03 / Track
thriveimage4.png — row 04 / Insight
thriveimage5.png — row 05 / Manage

For each of the 5 feature rows, find the
visual demo panel div (the side that
currently contains mock UI like athlete
cards, inbox messages, pipeline rows etc).

Replace the entire contents of that panel
with this image structure:

Row 01 — replace panel contents with:
<div style="
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  min-height: 340px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 24px;
">
  <img
    src="/Users/[yourusername]/Desktop/thrive stuff/thriveimage1.png"
    alt="Team Thrive Profile"
    style="
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 420px;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 16px;
      display: block;
      box-shadow:
        0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.5),
        0 0 0 1px rgba(0,229,160,0.1),
        0 8px 24px rgba(0,229,160,0.08);
    "
  />
</div>

Repeat this exact structure for rows
02 through 05, only changing the
image number in the filename.

To get the correct username for the
path, run this command in the terminal:
echo $HOME
Use the result as the base path so the
full path becomes:
$HOME/Desktop/thrive stuff/thriveimage1.png

Use that resolved absolute path for
all 5 image src attributes.

After replacing all 5 panels:

1. Make sure each feature row uses the
   same layout — text on one side, image
   on the other, alternating left/right.
   Odd rows (01, 03, 05): text left, image right.
   Even rows (02, 04): text right, image left.

2. Set consistent padding on every
   feature row section:
   padding-top: 80px;
   padding-bottom: 80px;

3. Set consistent gap between text
   and image columns on every row:
   gap: 60px;

4. Make the text column and image column
   equal width:
   grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
   or
   flex: 1; on both sides.

5. The image container div should have:
   display: flex;
   align-items: center;
   justify-content: center;

6. Every image gets this same shadow —
   do not remove it, it makes the cards
   float off the background:
   box-shadow:
     0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.5),
     0 0 0 1px rgba(0,229,160,0.1),
     0 8px 24px rgba(0,229,160,0.08);

Do not change any text content, feature
headings, pill tags, or section structure.
Only replace the visual panels and
standardize the spacing.